-- 
Ten Tourists Slightly Injured in Turkey Beach Blast, HT Says

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-28T11:34:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/ten-tourists-slightly-injured-in-turkey-beach-blast-ht-says.html
Ten tourists were slightly injured
when explosives hidden in rocks on a popular tourist beach in
 Turkey  exploded,  Haberturk  reported.  The explosion occurred on a beach in Kemer, a tourist
village near the Mediterranean town of Antalya, Haberturk said.
The explosive was hidden near the beach and sent rocks spraying
toward tourists who were sunbathing nearby, injuring ten, none
of them seriously, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  